# Gmail Configuration
GMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
GMAIL_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-here
GMAIL_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret-here
GMAIL_REFRESH_TOKEN=your-refresh-token-here

# To get the GMAIL_REFRESH_TOKEN, follow these steps:
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select an existing one
# 3. Enable the Gmail API
# 4. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials using the Client ID and Secret provided above
# 5. Add authorized redirect URI: https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground
# 6. Go to OAuth Playground: https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground/
# 7. Click the gear icon (settings) and check "Use your own OAuth credentials"
# 8. Enter your Client ID and Client Secret
# 9. In Step 1, select "Gmail API v1" and scope "https://mail.google.com/"
# 10. Click "Authorize APIs"
# 11. In Step 2, click "Exchange authorization code for tokens"
# 12. Copy the "Refresh token" value and paste it above
